# Admin Module Implementation — Based on System Requirements

You are tasked with completing the Admin UI for the "Best Class Evaluation & Verification System".

## Context
This system evaluates and ranks classes based on multiple criteria. The Admin defines and controls the entire evaluation structure. All configurations must be dynamic and stored (not hardcoded).

---

## 1. Academic Year Management
Implement UI to:
- Create a new academic year (e.g., 2025–26)
- Activate / deactivate an academic year
- Ensure only one active academic year at a time
- Switch between academic years (context-aware UI)

Requirements:
- Data must be separated by academic year
- Previous year data must remain unchanged

---

## 2. Criteria Management
This is the most critical module.

Implement:
- Add new criteria (e.g., Academics, Internships)
- Add sub-criteria under each criterion
- Edit / delete criteria and sub-criteria
- Maintain hierarchy (Criterion → Sub-criterion)
- Maintain history per academic year

UI Requirements:
- Display criteria in structured format (tree/table)
- Show max marks per sub-criterion
- Inline editing or modal-based editing

Constraints:
- Criteria must be dynamic (not hardcoded)
- Criteria must be fetched based on selected academic year

---

## 3. Marks Configuration
Implement:
- Assign marks for each sub-criterion
- Set maximum score limit per criterion

Validation:
- Marks must not exceed defined maximum
- Marks must be editable and stored in database

---

## 4. Lock Criteria Feature
Implement:
- Ability to lock criteria once evaluation begins

UI:
- Provide clear "Lock Criteria" action
- Add confirmation dialog before locking

Constraint:
- Once locked, criteria cannot be edited

---

## 5. User & Role Management
Implement:
- Create users
- Assign roles (Student, Teacher, Evaluation Team, HOD, IQAC, Admin)
- Edit / delete users

UI:
- Table view with filters (by role, department)
- Add/Edit via modal

---

## 6. Dashboard Overview (Admin)
Implement:
- Summary of:
  - Total classes
  - Submission status
  - Evaluation progress
- Display active academic year

---

## 7. System Constraints
Ensure:
- Only Admin can modify criteria
- Criteria are tied to academic year
- System supports dynamic configuration
- No hardcoded values for marks or criteria

---

## Goal
Build a clean, structured Admin UI that allows full control over:
- Academic years
- Evaluation criteria
- Marks configuration
- User roles

The UI should minimize friction and clearly represent system structure.